ğŸ”„ Marketing Funnel & Customer Journey
________________________________________
ğŸ¯ What is a Marketing Funnel?
A Marketing Funnel is a model that illustrates the stages a customer goes through before making a purchase.
Visualize it like a funnel: many people enter at the top, but only a few convert into customers at the bottom.
________________________________________
ğŸ“ Main Stages of the Marketing Funnel
Stage	Customer Mindset	Your Goal
1. Awareness	"I just found out about this."	Grab attention through ads, SEO, blogs
2. Interest	"This looks interesting."	Educate with content, emails, videos
3. Desire	"I think I need this."	Build desire through reviews, testimonials, comparison
4. Action	"Iâ€™ll buy it!"	Make it easy to purchase â€” clear CTAs, discounts, limited offers
5. Loyalty (optional stage)	"I love this brand."	Retain through rewards, support, and updates
________________________________________
ğŸ’¡ The AIDA Model (Popular Funnel Concept)
AIDA Stage	Explanation	Example
A â€“ Attention	Capture interest	Social Media Ads, Viral Content
I â€“ Interest	Keep them engaged	Blog posts, Product Demos
D â€“ Desire	Show value & benefits	Testimonials, Reviews, Offers
A â€“ Action	Convert to customer	Buy Now button, Checkout Page
________________________________________
ğŸ§­ What is a Customer Journey?
The Customer Journey maps the full experience of the customer with a brand â€” before, during, and after the purchase.
Think of it as the customerâ€™s story, not just a sales process.
________________________________________
ğŸ›£ï¸ Stages of the Customer Journey
Stage	Description
1. Awareness	Discovering your brand for the first time
2. Consideration	Comparing options and researching solutions
3. Purchase	Making the decision to buy
4. Retention	Staying engaged and loyal
5. Advocacy	Recommending to others â€” becoming a brand ambassador
________________________________________
ğŸ¤ Funnel vs. Journey â€“ Key Difference
â€¢	Funnel is business-focused: how to move people to purchase
â€¢	Journey is customer-focused: their experience at every touchpoint
________________________________________
ğŸ“Š Tools to Visualize Funnels & Journeys
â€¢	Google Analytics (User flow)
â€¢	HubSpot or Salesforce CRM
â€¢	Journey Mapping Tools like Miro, Lucidchart
